We have no such plans.  The library is designed so that concurrency control is outside its scope.  If I needed it for an application, I might consider using some application level code that looks like:<p><pre><code>    bool CAS(db, key, oldvalue, newvalue) {
      lock some mutex;
      read key's value from db;
      bool result = (value == oldvalue);
      if (result) write key=>newvalue to db;
      unlock;
      return result;
    }
</code></pre>
This should be not much slower than any hard-wired CAS we could provide from inside leveldb.
